questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput financial ledger application occasionally loses transaction records under heavy load. A custom concurrent staging class is used to buffer transactions before persisting them to the database. The class is managed by Spring and is defined as follows:

java
@Service
public class TransactionStager {
    private final Map<String, Transaction> stage = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    @Transactional
    public void stageAndCommit(String txId, Transaction tx) {
        stage.computeIfAbsent(txId, id -> {
            validate(tx); 
            persistToDatabase(tx); 
            return tx;
        });
    }

    private void validate(Transaction tx) {}
    private void persistToDatabase(Transaction tx) {}
}


During peak traffic, thread dumps show severe thread starvation and database transaction timeouts.
